begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation we talked about dogs. She has a poodle in a guide dog program and is watching her grandma's cocker spaniel.
middle_memory_text: We talked about COVID and how her state isn't doing great. And that PA is a swing state.
end_memory_text: We talked about food and video games.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week I literally have no idea about. I think it will be good. Anything beats this past week. I have a hearing due in a few days so I am stressed and nervous about that. I am very tired because I had a huge lesson plan due today.
critical_positive: I think we were in the same age bracket which made it easier to talk to her. I think we had similar interests like food and video games so it was good to talk about that. I think I lead most of the conversation which is ok I didn't mind.
critical_negative: I would have liked to know her political views because I didn't want to say anything controversial that she didn't like so I tried to mostly stay away from politics. I also would have liked to know her age and background but that feels weird to ask a person online. I don't want to come off as creepy.

begin_memory_text: We talk about dogs! They have a rescue dog who was adorable, so we chatted about that and how I am raising a service dog. I also learned that they have pet rats which is something we have in common! And they talked about how they are allergic to several animals.
middle_memory_text: We talked about school and COVID for a while. They are going to school for music and they play the trombone. We also discussed eating and some food we each enjoy. They really like pizza pringles. I got a laugh out of them drinking water out of a vase, too. They are high risk for COVID so discussed how they have been social distancing.
end_memory_text: We discussed New York state a lot since that is where they live. I told them I'm interested in vacationing there, so they talked a bit about what is in the state and several festivities held in the state. They have never been to New York City despite living in the state, and we both talked about the state of COVID in that area at the moment.
rest_of_day_open: I have a pretty relaxing end of the week! I will be spending a lot of time outdoors enjoying nature, or relaxing in my house watching TV to wrap up a rather busy and stressful week. I plan to spend a lot of time with my dogs, eat junk food, and get a little work done here and there.
critical_positive: I believe we had quite a bit in common, which helped keep the conversation rolling. It didn't feel like 30 minutes had passed, which tells me we got along pretty well! If there was a bit of a pause, one of us filled it almost immediately to keep things going.
critical_negative: I felt like my conversation partner wanted to take the lead a lot, which is ok, but it felt like when I spoke they wanted to be talking rather than listening. That may have just been them wanting to fill the space, or anxiety (I can talk more when I get anxious, too), but it did feel a little like they didn't care about the conversation.
